<article>
    <h1>Su&#xAD;per&#xAD;mar&#xAD;kets should take cue from Gi&#xAD;ant&#x2019;s move</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200926/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-26"><time>2020-09-26</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>I ap­plaud su­per­mar­ket chain Gi­ant’s ini­tia­tive to re­duce the prices of 650 daily es­sen­tials for six months (Gi­ant to lower prices of es­sen­tials for 6 months, Sept 24).</p>
    <p>Every cent counts, es­pe­cially dur­ing this pe­riod of hard­ship and un­cer­tainty due to the on­go­ing Covid-19 pan­demic.</p>
    <p>Many peo­ple have been hard hit by the loss of jobs and pay cuts, and pru­dence is the or­der of the day.</p>
    <p>Low­er­ing the prices of es­sen­tial food items will cer­tainly help strengthen the fam­ily meal bud­get.</p>
    <p>Be­sides Gi­ant’s price re­duc­tion move and FairPrice’s price freeze of 100 house brand items, I hope other ma­jor su­per­mar­ket chains will fol­low suit (FairPrice freezes prices of 100 daily es­sen­tials till year end, June 23).</p>
    <p>All th­ese ben­e­fits will help cush­ion the fi­nan­cial hard­ship dur­ing the eco­nomic down­turn.</p>
    <p>More than any­thing else, such a benev­o­lent move is a piv­otal part of cor­po­rate so­cial re­spon­si­bil­ity of a large busi­ness cor­po­ra­tion.</p>
    <p>Jef­frey Law Lee Beng</p>


</article>

